                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "Each 10 mg of caecal content sample was extracted by a 2-step extraction. An aliquot of 200-\u00b5l methanol/water (1:1, containing 6 internal standards, CA-d4, LCA-d4, UDCA-d4, GCA-d4, GCDCA-d4, and glycodeoxycholic acid (GDCA)-d4, 50 nM respectively) was added to the sample. The sample was homogenized for 5 min and centrifuged at 13,200 x g at 4 \u00baC for 15 min. The supernatant was transferred into a 1.5-ml tube and the sample residue was further extracted by an aliquot of 200-\u00b5l methanol/acetonitrile (2:8, containing 6 internal standards as the first extraction solvent). After homogenization and centrifugation, the supernatant was transferred to the tube with the first extraction. The extraction mixture was vortexed for 3 min and centrifuged at 13,200 x g at 4 \u00baC for 15 min. The supernatant was then transferred to a sampling vial for analysis.",
